options.name: Mode
options.description: The game mode.

values.name: Singleplayer
values.description: A regular, one player seed

values.name: Co-op
values.description: Everyone plays the same seed, all items are shared

values.name: Multiworld
values.description: A multiplayer setting where players can find each other's items

options.name: Players
options.description: For multiworld, how many players are in the game.

options.name: Distinct Worlds
options.description: For multiworld, with settings that involve randomness, should the worlds have distinct properties (ER, MQ, price rando...).

options.name: Goal
options.description: The objective of the seed. The game will end when the specified goal is reached.

values.name: Any Final Boss
values.description: You can beat either Ganon or Majora.

values.name: Ganon
values.description: You must beat Ganon.

values.name: Majora
values.description: You must beat Majora.

values.name: Ganon & Majora
values.description: You must beat Ganon AND Majora. You can do so in any order.

values.name: Triforce Hunt
values.description: You must collect Triforce Pieces to win.

values.name: Triforce Quest
values.description: You must collect the three parts of the Triforce (Power, Courage and Wisdom) to win. Specific hints will guide you.

options.name: Triforce Goal
options.description: The amount of Triforce Pieces that are required to win.

options.name: Triforce Pieces
options.description: The total amount of Triforce Pieces in the item pool.

options.name: Logic
options.description: The guarantees you have regarding reachability of locations.

values.name: All Locations
values.description: Every location in the game can be reached. The seed can always be completed.

values.name: Beatable Only
values.description: Some items can be placed in locations that are never reacheable. The seed can always be completed.

values.name: No Logic
values.description: Items are placed completely at random. The seed might be unbeatable.

options.name: Item Pool
options.description: Change the item pool.

values.name: Plentiful
values.description: One extra copy of every major item. Heart containers only.

values.name: Normal
values.description: The regular item count for each game.

values.name: Scarce
values.description: One less of every major item. No Heart Pieces.

values.name: Minimal
values.description: Only one of each major item. No Heart Pieces or Containers.

values.name: Barren
values.description: Minimal item pool, plus every shuffled item that is not strictly required to reach the goal (beatable only) or any location (all locations) gets removed.

options.name: Generate Spoiler Log
options.description: Generate an extra downloadable text file with the location of every item in the seed as well as other information. It is recommended to enable this option.

options.name: Probabilistic Foolish Hints
options.description: If you don't know what this is, leave it ON

options.name: No Plando Hints
options.description: Prevents items that are part of a plando from being hinted

options.name: Hint Importance
options.description: Hints will tell if an item is foolish, sometimes required, or always required

options.name: Song Shuffle
options.description: Controls where songs can be obtained, in both games.

values.name: Song Locations
values.description: Only locations that contain songs in the vanilla games will have songs.

values.name: Anywhere
values.description: Songs can be placed anywhere.

options.name: Deku Tree as Adult
options.description: Allows access to the Deku Tree as adult.

options.name: Well as Adult
options.description: Allows access to the Well as adult.

options.name: Fire Temple as Child
options.description: Allows access to the Fire Temple as child.

options.name: Open Dungeons (MM)
options.description: Controls whether or not MM dungeons will need their respective song. Takes priority over Clear State

options.name: Clear State Dungeons (MM)
options.description: Controls whether or not MM dungeons will need their respectives songs in the cleared state

options.name: Kakariko Gate
options.description: Controls the behavior of the gate in Kakariko blocking Death Mountain as child

values.name: Closed
values.description: The gate will be closed until you show Zelda's Letter to the guard

values.name: Open
values.description: The gate will be open from the start

options.name: Open Zora's Domain Shortcut
options.description: Removes the ice blocking Zora's Domain in Lake Hylia as adult

options.name: King Zora
options.description: Controls the behavior of King Zora in Zora's Domain

values.name: Vanilla
values.description: You will need to present him Ruto's Letter in order to enter Zora's Fountain as both Child and Adult

values.name: Open (Adult Only)
values.description: Already on the side as Adult, granting free Zora's Fountain access. Child still needs Ruto's Letter

values.name: Open
values.description: He will already be on the side for both Child and Adult, and Ruto's Letter is replaced by an empty bottle

options.name: Gerudo Fortress
options.description: Controls the behavior of the Carpenters in Gerudo Fortress

values.name: Vanilla
values.description: You will need to rescue all carpenters.

values.name: One Carpenter
values.description: You will need to rescue only one carpenter.

values.name: Open
values.description: Carpenters are rescued from the start and the bridge in Gerudo Valley as adult is repaired.

options.name: Skip Child Zelda
options.description: This changes the beginning of the child trade quest. True means you'll start having already met Zelda and got her item along with the one from Impa. The Chicken is also removed from the game, but Malon will still be at Hyrule Castle

options.name: Skip Oath to Order
options.description: Skip playing Oath to Order to reach the Moon.

options.name: Light Arrow Cutscene
options.description: Controls how the Light Arrow Cutscene should be triggered

values.name: Vanilla
values.description: Triggers at Temple of Time with Shadow and Spirit Medallions

values.name: Custom
values.description: Triggers at Temple of Time with a special condition

options.name: Rainbow Bridge
options.description: Controls how the Rainbow Bridge should be triggered

values.name: Open
values.description: The Rainbow Bridge is always open

values.name: Vanilla
values.description: Opens when you have the Light Arrows, Shadow Medallion, and Spirit Medallion

values.name: Medallions
values.description: Opens when you have all Medallions

values.name: Custom
values.description: You will need to meet a special condition to open the bridge

options.name: Majora Child Requirements
options.description: Controls the requirements to enter Majora's arena

values.name: None
values.description: As soon as you have access to the Moon you can enter Majora's arena

values.name: Custom
values.description: You will need to meet a special condition to enter Majora's arena

options.name: Boss Warp Pads
options.description: Controls the behavior of the MM Boss Warp Pads.

values.name: Boss Beaten
values.description: Enabled when the boss is beaten

values.name: Remains
values.description: Enabled when the matching remain is obtained

options.name: Free Scarecrow (OoT)
options.description: Allows to spawn Pierre the Scarecrow just by pulling the Ocarina out

options.name: Pre-Completed Dungeons
options.description: Allow dungeons to be pre-completed depending on rules.

options.name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Major)
options.description: How many major dungeons sould be pre-completed. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

options.name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Stones)
options.description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one stone, until it reaches that many stones. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

options.name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Medallions)
options.description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one medallion, until it reaches that many medallions. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

options.name: Pre-Completed Dungeons (Remains)
options.description: Pre-completes dungeons containing at least one remain, until in reaches that many remains. Can be combined with other pre-completed dungeon rules.

options.name: Open Mask Shop at night
options.description: Makes the Mask Shop in Market open during the night

options.name: Cross-Games Age
options.description: When you enter MM as Adult Link, you will be Adult Link in MM.

options.name: Cross-Games OoT Warp Songs
options.description: Allows you to play OOT Warp Songs from MM to warp to their respective locations. Logic could even expect you to do so

options.name: Cross-Games MM Song of Soaring
options.description: Controls whether you can play Song of Soaring from OOT to warp to MM Owl Statues and how logic should be affected

values.name: None
values.description: Song of Soaring is fully disabled in OOT

values.name: Child Only
values.description: Song of Soaring in OOT is enabled and logical only for Child

values.name: Child & Adult
values.description: Song of Soaring in OOT is enabled and logical for both Child and Adult

options.name: Container Appearance Matches Content

values.name: Never
values.description: Containers will be vanilla

values.name: Stone of Agony
values.description: Containers will match content when you have the Stone of Agony in OoT

values.name: Always
values.description: Containers will always match content

options.description: Modifies the chest, grass, and pot appearance so that they match their content. Works for unique items, keys, fairies, and souls. Grass and pots will otherwise always be gold if the item has not been collected

options.name: CAMC for Heart Pieces/Containers
options.description: Use a specific texture for heart pieces/containers

options.name: Skulltula CAMC
options.description: Enables CAMC for shuffled Gold, Swamp, and Ocean Skulltulas

options.name: Blast Mask Cooldown
options.description: Changes the cooldown between each explostion of the Blast Mask

options.name: Clock Speed
options.description: Alters the speed of the clock. Some options may render seeds unbeatable due to being unable to do time-related checks

values.name: Very Slow
values.description: The time will flow 66% slower than usual

values.name: Slow
values.description: The time will flow 33% slower than usual

values.name: Default
values.description: The normal clock speed

values.name: Fast
values.description: The clock speed will twice as fast than usual

values.name: Very Fast
values.description: USE AT OWN RISK!! - The clock speed will be 3x faster than usual, even on inverted

values.name: Super Fast
values.description: USE AT OWN RISK!! - The clock speed will be 6x faster than usual, even on inverted

options.name: Auto-Invert Time (MM)
options.description: Auto-inverts time at the start of a cycle

options.name: Fierce Deity Anywhere in MM
options.description: Controls the ability to use Fierce Deity outside of boss lairs. No logical applications

options.name: Hookshot Anywhere (OoT)
options.description: Modifies all surfaces to be hooked onto and if it is expected in logic

options.name: Hookshot Anywhere (MM)
options.description: Modifies all surfaces to be hooked onto and if it is expected in logic

options.name: Climb Most Surfaces (OoT)
options.description: Modifies most surface to be climbable and if it is expected in logic

options.name: Climb Most Surfaces (MM)
options.description: Modifies most surface to be climbable

options.name: Fast Bunny Hood
options.description: Modifies the Bunny Hood in OoT to give a speed increase

options.name: Default Hold Target
options.description: Forces the default target system to HOLD instead of SWITCH

options.name: Disable Crit Wiggle
options.description: Disables the camera zoom-in and weird movements when low on health

options.name: Restore Broken Actors
options.description: In vanilla OoT, some actors fails to load properly in some rooms due to errors in the room files. When this is on, these actors will load.

options.name: Alter Lost Woods Exits
options.description: There are unused exits in the Lost Woods that return you to the lost woods. When this is on, all the "got lost" exits in the Lost Woods that would normally take you to Kokiri Forest instead take you back to the Lost Woods, keeping your compass direction intact.

options.name: Void Warp in MM
options.description: In vanilla OoT, various code only checks for transitionTrigger, but in MM it also checks for transitionMode. When this is on, MM will no longer check transitionMode in those circumstances.

options.name: Fill Wallets
options.description: Fills the wallet upon finding a new one

options.name: OoT Shields
options.description: Alters OOT Shields behavior

values.name: Separate
values.description: They can be found independently from each other

values.name: Progressive
values.description: Each Progressive Shield will grant you the next one: Deku Shield -> Hylian Shield -> Mirror Shield. Other Deku and Hylian Shields do not count towards this chain, only the Progressive Shield item.

options.name: OoT Swords
options.description: Alters OOT Swords behavior

values.name: Separate
values.description: They can be found independently from each other

values.name: Progressive Knife and Biggoron
values.description: Kokiri Sword and Master Sword are independent. However Giant's Knife and Biggoron Sword are progressive.

values.name: Progressive
values.description: Each Progressive Sword will grant you the next one: Kokiri Sword -> Master Sword -> Giant's Knife -> Biggoron Sword

options.name: MM Shields
options.description: Alters MM Shields behavior

values.name: Separate
values.description: They can be found independently from each other

values.name: Progressive
values.description: Each Progressive Shield will grant you the next one: Hero Shield -> Mirror Shield. Other Hero Shields do not count towards this chain, only the Progressive Shield item. If shields are shared, Hero Shield will be obtained alongside Hylian Shield

options.name: MM Great Fairy Sword
options.description: Controls whether Great Fairy Sword is included in sword progression

options.name: MM Goron Lullaby
options.description: Alters the behavior of Goron Lullaby

values.description: Only the Goron Lullaby can be found, and when playing with Songs on Song Locations, Baby Goron in MM is no longer a Song Location

values.name: Progressive
values.description: Lullaby Intro will be received first before getting the full song

options.name: Clocks

values.name: Separate
values.description: Clocks will be independant of each other. If you don	 select a starting clock, one will be given to you at random.

values.name: Ascending
values.description: Clocks will be received in ascending order.

values.name: Descending
values.description: Clocks will be received in descending order.

options.name: Random Bottle Contents

options.name: Sunlight Arrows
options.description: Gives the OOT Light Arrows the ability to activate most sun switches

options.name: Bottomless Wallets
options.description: Adds a Wallet that can hold up to 9999 rupees in each game

options.name: Boss Entrance Shuffle
options.description: Shuffle bosses either within their own game or across both

options.name: Dungeon Entrance Shuffle
options.description: Enable the ability to shuffle dungeons within their own game or across both.

options.name: Wallmaster Shuffle
options.description: Enables the ability for Wallmasters to take you to random locations within their own game or across both games, based on other entrance settings

options.name: Shuffle Major Dungeons with Dungeons
options.description: If turned on, it means the boss-containing dungeons and uninverted Stone Tower Temple will be shuffled.

options.name: Shuffle OoT Minor Dungeons with Dungeons
options.description: If turned on, it means Bottom of the Well, Ice Cavern and Gerudo Training Grounds are also shuffled

options.description: If paired with another dungeon shuffle, allows saving from the Quest Menu with L/C-Up while on the Clock Tower Roof.

options.name: Shuffle Beneath The Well with Dungeons
Shuffle Ikana Castle Interior with Dungeons
Shuffle Major Regions
options.description:
- Every entrance to Hyrule Field except Market
- The entrance to Gerudo Fortress from Gerudo Valley
- The entrance to Death Mountain from Kakariko
- The entrances to the four main regions in MM
- The entrance to Romani Ranch

options.name: Shuffle Market Entrance
options.description: Shuffle Hyrule Field's Market entrance among the regions.

options.name: Shuffle Regional Shortcuts
options.description:
Shuffles the various shortcuts between regions.
- Lost Woods/Goron City
- Lost Woods/Zora's River
- Zora's Domain/Lake Hylia

options.name: Shuffle Interiors
options.description: Enable the ability to shuffle interiors in their own game or across both games.

options.name: Shuffle Most Interiors
options.description: Shuffle most interiors with each other.

options.name: Shuffle Extra Interiors
options.description:
Shuffle additional, more complex interiors. These include:
- OOT: Link's House, Temple of Time, Windmill, Kak Potion Shop
- MM: Stock Pot Inn, Astral Observatory/Bombers' Hideout, Swamp Tourist Hut, Ikana Spring Cave

options.name: Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring

values.name: None
values.description: Warp songs and soaring are not shuffled.

values.name: OoT Only
values.description: Shuffles only OoT's warp songs among each other.

values.name: MM Only
values.description: Shuffles only MM's soaring spots among each other.

values.name: Own Game
values.description: Shuffles both warp songs and soaring spots within their own game.

values.name: Full
values.description: Shuffles both warp songs and soaring spots together.

options.description: Allows separate shuffling of the warp songs and soaring spots. This setting is disabled if both are selected in "Shuffle One-Way Entrances".

options.name: Shuffle One-Way Entrances

values.name: None
values.description: One-Way entrances are not shuffled.

values.name: Own Game
values.description: One-Way entrances are only shuffled among their own game.

values.name: Full
values.description: One-Way entrances can be shuffled among both games.

options.description: Enables the option of shuffling various one-way entrances.

options.name: Shuffle Standard One-Ways
options.description: Shuffles the Gerudo Valley to Lake Hylia and Ikana Canyon to Southern Swamp entrances.

options.name: Shuffle Ikana Castle One-Ways
options.description: Shuffles the one-way entrances in Ikana Castle with the others. This is the keg-blocked entrance and the block moved by the switch.

options.name: Shuffle One-Ways with Warp Songs
options.description: Shuffles the warp songs from OOT among one-way entrances. This setting is disabled if the warp songs are shuffled with "Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring".

options.name: Shuffle One-Ways with Owl Statues
options.description: Shuffles the owl statues from MM among one-way entrances. This setting is disabled if the soaring spots are shuffled with "Shuffle Warp Songs and Soaring".

options.name: Shuffle Child Owl Flights
options.description: Shuffle the two owl flights among one-way entrances.

options.name: Shuffle Altered Lost Woods Exits
options.description: Shuffle the Lost Woods entrances added by "Alter Lost Woods Exits" among one-way entrances.
